commit.message:
Fix the build for cygwin. Thanks to Andrew Lynch <andrew.lynch@dayton99.com>
for lighting a fire under me to finally try getting this to work, and to
Pierre A. Humblet <Pierre.Humblet@ieee.org> for assistance in getting things
to build against minires.

* configure.in: Add a check for a combination of libminires and libiphlpapi,
  which provide a simple stub resolver for cygwin programs. The check is for
  __res_query rather than the res_query macro, to handle the manner in which
  autoconf constructs test cases.
Quick change to Filename tags for directories.
Forgot to remove dead tests.
General documentation updates.
Removed files which are autogenerated by the development build environment.
Removing maps and orbs tests, since neither is still around.
Forgot to update the RPM spec file for the new "rbl" script.

Add information about the "rbl" script.
Reformat the "Using" chapter to flow a little better.

rbl.in: Adding '-c' is a little harsh. Let the user decide.
rblcheck.c: Cosmetic touch-up.

New script: rbl (command-line wrapper for rblcheck which parses both
${sysconfdir}/rblcheckrc and ${HOME}/.rblcheckrc for arguments; intended
to ease maintenance of commonly-used lists of RBL services).
Pulling out ORBS tests, since ORBS is dead.
Quick update reflecting ORBS' departure.

Updated the new ORBS children and marked the ORBS zone as offline.
Updated the URL to Mike Stump's blacklist. (Aren't we all glad Google acquired Deja?)
Added new notes about building a development release.
Re-adding my own copy -- couldn't get automake build to work without this.

Upped the version number so as to reflect that this is "totally
new". (Should have done so already when first checking in; sorry for
being so messy.)

Significantly fixed the actual contents -- should not have been so
quick to commit anything to begin with. (Sorry for being so messy.)

This is probably still slightly erroneous and/or incomplete. (Sorry
for being so messy.)
Placeholder for something which either used to exist, or is going to ...
Added a few to-do list items.

Must learn to read before committing. ;-P rfc-ignorant.org is domain-based,
not address-based.
Added rfc-ignorant.org to the list of sites.
Coulda sworn I added Marco to the credits ages ago...sorry!
Bugfix from Marco d'Itri <md@Linux.IT>; check res_query() return, not h_errno.
A few typo and thinko fixes from the Solaris packaging commit.

Added a "make solarispkg" target for building a Solaris package automatically.
Moved rblcheck.spec.in into config directory. Seemed more fitting.

Added an RPM spec file for the "make dist" target, updated ChangeLog.
Fixed a docs/Makefile.am error that the RPM build turned up.
"-Wall" does wonders, doesn't it? ;-) Cleared out unused variables.
Added Makefile.am to generate .html, .ps, and .rtf versions of the documentation with "make dist".
Make sure everything "important" in installed with "make dist".

First attempt at a test suite ("make check" to try it).
Updated documentation.
Usage output fix.
